Gocław is a subdistrict in Praga-Południe, in south-east Warsaw with a population of over 50,000 inhabitants.
Neighbourhoods
The area of Gocław is divided into six separate neighborhoods (osiedla):
* Iskra
* Jantar
* Orlik
* Wilga
* Kępa Gocławska
